We model extrinsic noise by perturbing the reaction rate parameters, using a Gaussian kernel, before each simulation of the model [35, 38]. The effect of extrinsic noise on each reaction is assumed to be independent. The reaction rates associated with a particular gene are termed nominal parameters (θn). 
